McLaughlin &amp; Harvey, the County Antrim-based construction group, said that
Mr Eric Bell and Mr Philip Sykes of BDO Binder Hamlyn had been appointed
joint administrative receivers. The company's shares were suspended at 28p.
McLaughlin, which incurred losses of Pounds 6.8m (Pounds 5.4m) in 1992, had
earlier said it was in consultation with its principal bankers.
</TEXT>
