<HEADLINE>
FT  08 OCT 93 / Gallup sees hope in housing market
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER MARSH
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
INTEREST in buying houses and flats was last month at its highest level for
two years, according to a survey by Gallup, the market-research group, Peter
Marsh writes.
An index used by Gallup to illustrate people's readiness to inquire about
house purchases was 13.63 in September - after 12.08 in August. Gallup said
the rise in house-buying interest in recent months was 'consistent with a
modest price recovery' in housing.
However, it added that 'a significant minority' in its monthly poll of 2,000
people were being put off buying homes by fears about unemployment, lack of
savings and insufficient income.
People wishing to buy for the first time are more bullish about entering the
market than those already owning homes, the report says.
