FT  08 OCT 93 / New broadcasting union leader
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MR Roger Bolton has been elected general secretary of Bectu, the
broadcasting union. He won by more than 1,000 votes from Mr Roy Lockett, his
nearest rival, who will continue as the union's deputy general secretary.
He takes over from Mr Tony Hearn who is retiring at the end of the month. Mr
Bolton has been leading union opposition to the BBC's controversial Producer
Choice. This policy, introduced earlier this year, encourages
programme-makers to invite tenders for crews and studios from private-sector
companies.
