FT  08 OCT 93 / Water price deals proposed
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BRONWEN MADDOX
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
FOUR more water companies have proposed deals with Ofwat, the water
regulator, that would reduce the scope for varying each year's price rises,
Bronwen Maddox writes.
Ofwat, which sets the annual price rises, has sometimes requested companies
to restrain increases, while companies have sometimes negotiated extra rises
to cover unexpected costs.
Under the proposed deals between Ofwat and Southern Water, North East Water,
Essex Water and Suffolk Water price rises will be more predictable. Similar
deals have been made with five other companies.
Next year Ofwat will review the industry's pricing structure and will set
price rises for 1995 to 2005.
