FT  08 OCT 93 / Nottinghamshire exports fall
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
COMPANIES IN Nottinghamshire have suffered a sharp decline in export orders
with the worsening recession in continental Europe, the county's chamber of
commerce said yesterday.
The number of companies reporting increased overseas sales in the last
quarter fell to the lowest level since September 1991, according to the
chamber's latest economic survey. Domestic orders, however, have improved
with 42 per cent of companies reporting rising UK demand, a 17 percentage
point increase on the same quarter last year.
