<HEADLINE>
FT  07 OCT 93 / BIS warning on capital curbs
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BRUSSELS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Controls on the movement of money will not repair the European Community's
punctured currency grid, Mr Alexandre Lamfalussy, general manager of the
Basle-based Bank for International Settlements said yesterday, Reuter
reports from Brussels.
'International financial integration has encompassed practically the whole
world . . . It would be neither desirable nor indeed technically feasible to
isolate Europe from the rest of the world in this respect,' Mr Lamfalussy
told a hearing on money market speculation at the European Parliament.
</TEXT>
