FT  07 OCT 93 / Observer: Cash in hand
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Severely strapped for cash, Conservative party officials are having to
become pretty resourceful in their quest to turn an extra penny. But the
prize so far must go to the loyal workers in treasury minister Stephen
Dorrell's seat of Loughborough.
They are spending the week at the annual conference seeking out prominent
Euro-sceptics to autograph Teresa Gorman's new book, The Bastards, billed as
the inside story of the Euro-sceptics' revolt against Maastricht 'and how
