Neil Hamilton, Lord Tebbit, the former party chairman, who further
identifies himself as 'one who knows who his father is', and John Carlisle,
the MP for Luton North, who appends the legend 'barmy'. Thatcherite chief
treasury secretary Michael Portillo is understood to have declined to lend
his name to the endeavour.
The views of ardently pro-European Dorrell on this display of local
initiative are not known.
